# Cheap Copilot profile overlay (seven-pack topology)

Read this when launched with `swarmforge/profiles/cheap-copilot-seven-pack.conf`.

## Purpose
This profile uses mini/flash Copilot models. The **specifier is present but idle by default** — too costly and too weak here for reliable new specs. Execute **already-specced** backlog items only.

## Coordinator — intake and routing (critical)
- **Do not route parcels to the specifier** in normal operation. No `git_handoff` or `note` to specifier for new work, backlog drain, or promotion follow-up.
- **Work the existing queue:** promote eligible items from `backlog/paused/` into `backlog/active/` (respect `active_backlog_max_depth`), then route **directly to coder**.
- Prefer mechanical routing when the active item is ready:
  ```sh
  swarmforge/scripts/route_backlog_to_coder.sh [BL-id]
  ```
- If a parcel is already in flight downstream (coder..QA), chase and unblock — do not restart via specifier.
- **Backlog root** (`backlog/*.yaml` not in `active/`/`paused/`/`done/`): do **not** send to specifier. Leave raw intake for the human or a stronger profile; note the human if root items are blocking progress.
- When `backlog/paused/` and `backlog/active/` are both empty, go idle — do not invent specifier work.
- Rule-proposals to specifier: only if a human explicitly asks; otherwise defer.

## Specifier on this profile
- Stay idle unless the **human** types directly into your pane or explicitly asks you to spec something.
- Do not self-assign backlog root drain on this profile — coordinator owns routing to coder for pre-specced work.

## Other roles
- Normal seven-pack chain after coder: cleaner → architect → hardender → documenter → QA → coordinator (integrate per PIPELINE.md).

## Handoffs
- Draft path: **`swarmforge/runtime/handoff-draft.txt`**
- Run: `swarmforge/scripts/swarm_handoff.sh swarmforge/runtime/handoff-draft.txt`
